DP) in 1997. In 1997 the road network had grown to 26,550km, of which 3,708km were paved. Then, as a result of investments made under the three phases of RSDP during the last 13 years the total length of the network has increased to 49,000 km. According to the thirteen years RSDP performance assessment document, out of the total network 22,247km is federal while the remaining 26,753 km is regional. The condition of the road network is also improved. Currently, almost 55% of the total classified road network is in good condition, 26% are registered as being in fair condition and the remaining 19% is considered to be poor.